This paper discusses the behavior of the duet measurement procedure in multiple cloud environments, which involves executing measured artifacts in parallel and evaluating their relative performance together. This procedure is relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC), performance analysis (cs.PF), programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), and architecture (cs.AR).
